Special read behaviors
	i. Removes data from the pipe
	ii. If the pipe is empty, it waits:
		- for some data to arrive 
		or 
		- for no writer to be connected to the pipe
	iii. returns the length of what it actually read
	
Special write behaviors
	i. Adds data to the pipe
	ii. If the pipe is full, it waits 
		- for some space to me made 
		or 
		- for no reader to be connected to the pipe
	iii. returns the length of what it actually wrote
	
	
CLOSE EACH PIPE AS SOON AS IT IS NOT NEEDED ANYMORE.
IT IS INHERITED FROM THE PARENT TO CHILD.
USE A SEPARATE PIPE FOR EACH DIRECTION OF COMMUNICATION.

